"What is the time complexity of building a heap from an array?
-------------------------------------------------------------
The time complexity of building a heap from an array (using the standard "heapify" or "bottom-up" approach) is O(n), where n is the number of elements in the array.
This is because, although each sift-down operation can take up to O(log n) time, most elements are near the bottom of the tree and require much less work. Summing the work across all nodes results in a total time of O(n), not O(n log n).
This is a classic result in algorithms and is more efficient than inserting each element one by one into an empty heap.

"Explain the difference between Pessimistic and Optimistic locking."
-------------------------------------------------------------------
Pessimistic: Locks data, prevents concurrent updates, but can reduce throughput.
Optimistic: No locks, detects conflicts at commit, better for high-concurrency/low-conflict scenarios.


"What are the four pillars of OOP, and how do they apply to a recent project you built?"
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Encapsulation: Bundling data (fields) and methods that operate on the data into a single unit (class),
and restricting direct access to some of the object's components.
Abstraction: Hiding complex implementation details and showing only the necessary features of an object.
Inheritance: Mechanism where one class acquires the properties and behaviors of another class.
Polymorphism: Ability to present the same interface for different underlying forms (data types).



