"The following Swift code has a race condition. Identify it and provide the thread-safe fix" ******
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Step 1: Identify the race condition Suppose the code is:
class Counter {
    var value = 0
    func increment() {
        value += 1
    }
}
If multiple threads call increment() at the same time, value can be corrupted because value += 1 is not atomic.

class Counter {
    private var value = 0
    private let lock = NSLock()
    func increment() {
        lock.lock()
        value += 1
        lock.unlock()
    }
}
The original code is not thread-safe because multiple threads can modify value at the same time, causing data races.
By adding a lock or using a serial queue, you ensure only one thread can modify value at a time, making it thread-safe.


